# Event-Driven Thinking

Instead of asking:

> "What pages exist?"

Ask:

> "What events happen?"

Events are easier to model.

Examples:

```
User Registered

↓

User Logged In

↓

Product Created

↓

Cart Updated

↓

Payment Started

↓

Payment Completed

↓

Order Created

↓

Order Shipped

↓

Order Delivered

↓

Review Added
```

Every event may:

* update the database,
* trigger notifications,
* create logs,
* affect analytics.

